main event: A sighting of an unidentified object occurred in Winchester, Massachusetts on July 2, 1956.
interesting points: The observed object was moving in a very light circle before changing direction,The object completed four 90 degree turns during the observation,Its speed was estimated at 700 MPH on a straight course,The color of the object was described as yellow-white,The object's shape was not discernible and its size was impossible to estimate.
